  <thing id="spNNWCGrPg" name="Curse of the Great Plague" description="This spell allows the caster to magically infect a body of water with the disease of his choice. The specific disease is chosen at the time of casting and must correspond with the bit of diseased material used as a spell component. As part of the spell, the caster must deposit the material in the desired body of water. Upon completion of the spell, all water within range of the spell that connects to the body of water where the material was deposited becomes infected with the disease. Any creature which drinks or swims in the water becomes exposed to the disease, regardless of how the disease is normally contracted (ie; contact, ingested, inhaled, injury). The creature saves versus the disease normally, but does not gain any additional saving throw from the spell itself." compset="Spell">
