  <thing id="spNNWMrwTr" name="Mirror Travel" description="By means of this spell the caster can move magically from mirror to mirror instantly. In order to cast this spell the caster must touch a mirror (any mirror will do, as long as it is a solid object with a particularly reflective surface. DMs have final say on what is, and is not, a mirror for the purposes of this spell) and recite the incantation, then select another mirror within 1,000 ft per caster level (to a maximum of 20,000 ft at 20th level). The caster and all equipment vanish into the first mirror and then emerge from the second mirror one round later. This spell does not grant perfect familiarity with all mirrors in the area, and you must have some clear idea of the location and layout of the destination. This functions the same as the spell teleport, except that the caster always emerges from a mirror of some kind." compset="Spell">
    <fieldval field="sTarget" value="Self"/>
