    <exprreq message="Vampiric Telepathy feat required"><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fNNWVampTl] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Cruomancer level 9"><![CDATA[hero.tagcount[Custom.NNWCruoman] >= 9]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fNNWVmpFlt" name="Vampiric Flight" description="{b}Benefit{/b}: As a standard action, by spending 2 blood points, you can grant yourself the power of flight. The source of your flight is either unseen magic, or large bat-like wings that erupt from your body and then fold back into it when the ability ends. When you gain this feat, you must determine which of the two source of flight you use. This choice cannot be changed. The two sources have slightly different effects, as outlined below:\n\n{i}Supernatural Flight{/i}: You gain a fly speed of 30 feet with a maneuverability of perfect. Your flight ends if you enter an anti-magic zone, but is unaffected by being paralyzed or otherwise unable to move.\n\n{i}Winged Flight{/i}: You gain a fly speed of 50 feet with a maneuverability of average. Your flight functions normally in an anti-magic zone, but ends immediately if you become paralyzed or otherwise unable to move.\n\nRegardless of the source of your flight, this ability lasts for 1 minute per cruomancer level you possess." compset="Feat" summary="You can call upon your vampiric nature to allow you to fly." uniqueness="useronce">
    <fieldval field="actName" value="Flight"/>
