      doneif (tagis[Helper.FtDisable] <> 0)

hero.child[aDEX].field[aStartMod].value += field[abValue].value
endif]]></eval>
    <eval phase="PostLevel" priority="40000" index="2">field[trkMax].value += hero.tagcount[Custom.NNWCruoman]</eval>
    <exprreq message="Cruomancer level 1"><![CDATA[hero.tagcount[Custom.NNWCruoman] >= 1]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fNNWVmpMIs" name="Vampiric Memory Insertion" description="{b}Benefit{/b}: As a standard action, by spending 2 blood points, you may touch a humanoid creature and implant one or more memories. This functions as modify memory, except that you must touch the target, you can affect an amount of memory equal to five minutes per cruomancer level you possess, and you can only add new memories, not erase or modify existing ones. As with modify memory, an implanted memory does not necessarily affect the target&apos;s actions, particularly if it contradicts the target&apos;s natural inclinations. An illogical modified memory is dismissed by the target as a bad dream, too much wine, or another similar excuse.\n\nIf your cruomancer level is 10 or higher, you may choose to spend 5 blood points when you activate this ability, instead of the normal amount. If you do, then it can affect any living creature with an Intelligence score of 3 or higher, instead of just humanoid creatures." compset="Feat" summary="You casually access the target&apos;s memories, adding new ones" uniqueness="useronce">
