  <thing id="fNNWVmpMVl" name="Vampiric Memory Veil" description="{b}Benefit{/b}: As a standard action, by spending 2 blood points, you may touch a humanoid creature and erase some of its memories. This functions as modify memory, except that you must touch the target, you can affect an amount of memory equal to five minutes per cruomancer level you possess, and you can only erase existing memories, not modify or add new memories. The saving throw DC to resist the effect is equal to 10 + 1/2 your cruomancer level + your Charisma modifier.\n\nIf your cruomancer level is 10 or higher, you may choose to spend 5 blood points when you activate this ability, instead of the normal amount. If you do, then it can affect any living creature with an Intelligence score of 3 or higher, instead of just humanoid creatures." compset="Feat" summary="You reach into the target&apos;s mind and obscure certain things" uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="srcLibVamp"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="NNWVampire"/>
