  <thing id="cHelpNN6" name="Vampire Hunter" description="The vampire hunter stands against the undead, travelling from town to town and protecting the people by fighting terrible, inhuman monsters that no one else is willing to stand against, and which more often than not turn out to be all too human. Though the vampire hunter specializes in fighting vampires, many of his talents allow him to take the battle to other kinds of undead with equal skill and precision.\n\n{b}Becoming a Vampire Hunter{/b}\n\nMost Vampire Hunters are fighters or rangers who, after deciding to specialize in battling vampires for whatever personal reason, enter the prestige class to gain a few useful tools for fighting their favored foes. Classes without a perfect base attack bonus can enter the class as well, but it will take them somewhat longer to be able to get in.\n\n{b}Entry Requirements{/b}\n\n{b}Base Attack{/b}: +5\n{b}Skills: Knowledge{/b}: (religion) 5 ranks\n{b}Special{/b}: Must have destroyed at least one full-fledged vampire (this includes vampires, revenants with a cruomancer level of at least 5, [feral vampires] and nosferatu, but not vampire spawn, [psychic vampires], [culled], or revenants with a cruomancer level of less than 5)\n\n{b}Class Features{/b}\n\n{b}Hit Dice{/b}: d10\n{b}Skills{/b}: Acrobatics, Craft (alchemy), Knowledge (religion), Perception, Stealth, Survival\n{b}Weapon and Armor Proficiency{/b}: Vampire hunters are proficient with all martial weapons, and with crossbows of all kinds. They gain no additional proficiency with armor or shields." compset="Class" summary="The vampire hunter stands against the undead" uniqueness="unique">
